<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1177" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1177">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Corea</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the Greater Republic of Central
                                        America</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington, D.
                                    C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-18"><hi rend="italic">July 18,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: To-day I have had the honor to receive
                            your esteemed communication of the 15th instant, which refers to the
                            rules to which neutral war vessels should conform that may desire to
                            enter or leave the ports blockaded now or which may be blockaded by the
                            United Stated during the war with Spain.</p>
                        <p>I have taken due note of referred-to communication, and by the next mail
                            I shall have the honor to communicate it to my Government.</p>
                        <p>I reiterate, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Luis F. Corea.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>